The paper focuses on extractive summarization for spoken documents, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques (cs.CL, cs.IR). The proposed methods aim to address the issue of coverage in summarization, which is a common concern in document summarization (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the use of different document/sentence representation methods to enhance summarization performance, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
